+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SQ2GWka4acHbHaSDkmWKuA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every file in this codebase. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Structure and Configuration\n\n**`/workspace/package.json`**\n- Name: `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- Type: ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n- Dependencies: `express` (v5), `marked` (v17), plus their `@types/` packages\n- Dev dependencies: `typescript` (v5.9), `vitest` (v2.1), `eslint` + `@typescript-eslint`\n\n**`/workspace/tsconfig.json`**\n- Strict mode, target ES2022, module Node16\n- `rootDir: ./src`, `outDir: ./dist`, declarations enabled\n\n**`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`**\n- Globals enabled (`globals: true`), test timeout 10 seconds\n\n**`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`**\n- Unused vars error except those prefixed with `_` (using `argsIgnorePattern: '^_'`)\n\n**File tree (non-.git):**\n```\nsrc/core/types.ts\nsrc/core/engine.ts\nsrc/core/templates.ts\nsrc/core/index.ts\nsrc/plugins/.gitkeep          (empty - plugins to be created here)\ntests/core.test.ts\ntests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts\ntests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts\ntests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts\ntests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts\ntests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts\ntests/plugins/search-index.test.ts\ntests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts\ntests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Complete Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Plugins have three lifecycle hooks: `beforeBuild`, `transformContent`, `afterBuild`\n- `transformContent` receives a single `ContentFile` and returns a (possibly modified) `ContentFile`\n- `BuildContext.data` is the shared inter-plugin communication channel (a `Map<string, unknown>`)\n- `BuildContext.output` is where generated files go (path string -> content string)\n- `BuildContext.assets` is for binary data (unused in tests, but available)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Core Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class orchestrates everything:\n\n1. **`registerPlugin(plugin)`** - pushes plugin onto internal array\n2. **`registerTemplate(template)`** - stores template by name in a Map\n3. **`resolvePluginOrder()`** - topological sort via DFS:\n   - Throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"` on cycles\n   - Throws `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"` for unregistered deps\n4. **`build(files)`** - the main pipeline:\n   - Creates `BuildContext` with copies of files, empty output/assets/data maps\n   - Resolves plugin order\n   - Runs `beforeBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Runs `transformContent` hooks in dependency order (each plugin transforms ALL files before the next plugin runs)\n   - Renders templates: looks up `file.template || 'default'`, calls `template.render(content, data)`, stores in `ctx.output` as `{slug}.html`. If no matching template, stores raw content.\n   - Runs `afterBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Returns the context\n\n---\n\n### 4. Core Templates (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n- **`createDefaultTemplate()`** - renders an article page with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n- **`createListTemplate()`** - renders with `<h1>` and `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Index (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`)\n\nRe-exports everything: `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) - 15 tests\n\nAll pass currently. They test:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. Default template rendering (HTML structure, title, content, site title)\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content output when no matching template\n6. `beforeBuild` hook invocation\n7. `transformContent` hook (uppercasing content)\n8. `afterBuild` hook invocation\n9. Dependency ordering (`a` before `b`)\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugins' `transformContent` applied in order\n13. Shared data store (`ctx.data`)\n14. File metadata retained through build\n15. Empty file list produces empty output\n\n---\n\n### 7. Plugin Test Files - Detailed Breakdown\n\n#### 7a. `markdown-ext` (Wave 1, no deps) - `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`\n- **Import**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n- **Hook used**: `transformContent`\n- **8 tests**:\n  1. Converts basic markdown (`# Hello`, `**bold**`) to HTML (`<h1>`, `<strong>`)\n  2. Footnotes: `[^1]` becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  3. Footnote section: `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` and `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>`\n  4. `:::note` container becomes `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n  5. `:::warning` container becomes `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`\n  6. `:::tip` container becomes `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`\n  7. Preserves existing HTML in content\n  8. Handles empty content\n\n#### 7b. `asset-pipeline` (Wave 1, no deps) - `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`\n- **Import**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n- **Hook used**: `transformContent`\n- **8 tests**:\n  1. Rewrites `src=\"./image.png\"` to `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n  2. Rewrites `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` to `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n  3. Leaves absolute URLs unchanged (e.g., `https://cdn.example.com/image.png`)\n  4. Generates `asset-manifest` in `ctx.data` with `{ assets: string[] }` containing filenames (e.g., `\"photo.jpg\"`)\n  5. No-op for files with no asset references\n  6. Handles multiple assets in one file (all appear in manifest)\n  7. Accumulates assets across multiple files (calling `transformContent` twice on different files)\n  8. Does NOT double-process already-rewritten URLs (`/assets/image.png` stays unchanged, manifest empty)\n\n#### 7c. `syntax-highlight` (Wave 1, no deps) - `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts`\n- **Import**: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n- **Hook used**: `transformContent`\n- **8 tests**:\n  1. Adds `highlighted` class: `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n  2. Adds `data-language=\"python\"` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n  3. Handles multiple code blocks (each gets its own `data-language`)\n  4. No-language code blocks left unchanged (no `highlighted`, no `data-language`)\n  5. Adds `highlighted` class to processed blocks\n  6. Preserves code block content\n  7. Handles empty code blocks (still gets `data-language` and `hi